WEBVTT

00:01.560 --> 00:02.320
Jake Green!

00:02.320 --> 00:03.840
How you doing, man?

00:03.840 --> 00:04.220
Wait a minute.

00:04.220 --> 00:06.170
--Where the hell you been?
--Around.

00:06.550 --> 00:08.730
Jake, no one's been around for five years.

00:08.730 --> 00:11.380
Seriously, where have you been?

00:12.160 --> 00:13.300
Hey, brother.

00:13.300 --> 00:14.670
What you put this family through...

00:14.676 --> 00:16.370
--Johnston, for God's sake.
--Now, he could have been...

00:16.372 --> 00:18.823
We could spend a week talking
about what I could have been, all right?

00:18.824 --> 00:21.996
--I've apologized, but I need my
money to make a clean start.
--It's not your money.

00:21.998 --> 00:23.306
It's your grandfather's money.

00:23.437 --> 00:26.880
--Stay one more day.
--I've got to get back to San Diego by tomorrow.

00:34.786 --> 00:37.642
All right, it looks like the explosion came
from the west, maybe Denver.

00:37.857 --> 00:39.022
Did something happen?

00:39.057 --> 00:39.952
Are we under attack?

00:40.228 --> 00:42.830
Hi, Dale. Sorry I didn't call
sooner, angel, but we...

00:42.835 --> 00:44.761
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

00:46.718 --> 00:48.972
Sheriff? Robert Hawkins.

00:48.975 --> 00:50.132
I am so sorry.

00:50.336 --> 00:53.292
--I didn't know your mother was in Denver.
--She wasn't in Denver.

00:53.297 --> 00:54.571
She was in Atlanta.

00:54.576 --> 00:55.402
Oh, my God!

00:55.646 --> 00:57.552
Look, I know you're telling people
it was an accident

00:57.566 --> 00:59.450
but if it was an attack, Sheriff

00:59.588 --> 01:01.310
and there's chaos out there,

01:01.508 --> 01:02.950
you might not want the wrong people knowing

01:02.957 --> 01:04.363
that Jericho is still here.

01:04.367 --> 01:05.450
It's the wrong bus!

01:06.796 --> 01:07.530
Riley!

01:09.268 --> 01:11.041
Get April.
We'll meet you at the medical center.

01:11.047 --> 01:12.612
There's an empty prison bus out there.

01:12.857 --> 01:15.271
--What's your name?
--Heather.

01:16.408 --> 01:17.420
Nice to meet you, Jake.

01:17.428 --> 01:20.702
--It's a great thing you did t there tonight.
--Thanks.

01:20.708 --> 01:23.273
Something happened in Denver, Atlanta,

01:23.408 --> 01:25.083
and it could be that we wake up

01:25.086 --> 01:26.873
and we find out that's where it stopped.

01:27.226 --> 01:28.191
But, until we know,

01:28.545 --> 01:31.441
are we going to use our imaginations
to solve problems

01:31.446 --> 01:32.451
or to cause them?

